"""Drift incident apply (phase 3b).

For an `approved-<letter>` incident: dispatch the chosen option's structured
`apply` plan to a handler, verify pre/post state, and update status to
`applied`. Idempotent — if the change is already in place, marks the incident
as applied without re-executing.

Usage:
  incident-apply <id>                  # apply the approved option
  incident-apply <id> --dry-run        # show what would happen, no writes
  incident-apply --all-approved        # apply every approved-* incident
  incident-apply <id> --no-post        # skip Drift ack

Handlers:
  cron-edit          : openclaw cron edit <id> --model X / --cron X / ...
  file-patch         : exact old_string→new_string replacement under allowlisted roots
                       (skill files under ~/.openclaw/skills/ are also covered here)
  routing-fix        : deep-merge into openclaw.json (channels.* or routing.* subtrees only)
  investigate, infrastructure : no-op (just mark applied with note)
"""
from __future__ import annotations

